 @usage <pre>
  var breakpoint= kony.application.getCurrentBreakpoint();
</pre>

getCurrentForm.!doc:
This API returns a handle to the current form. The form handle is useful when you are sending analytics to the analytic engine.
        @returns currentForm{Object}
        @Available Available on all platforms.
        @Usage <pre>function getCurrentForm()
{
    //Get the current form
    var currentForm = kony.application.getCurrentForm();
    //Alert the current form
    alert("currentForm is::"+currentForm);
}</pre>

getCurrentSettingsMenu.!doc:
This method returns the unique identifier of the current  menu that is set through getCurrentSettingsMenu.
    @Available Windows 8
    @usage <pre>kony.application.getCurrentSettingsMenu ();

//Alert the Current Charm Settings menu
alert("Current charm menu id is:: "+currCharmMenuId);</pre>

getPreviousForm.!doc:
This API returns a handle to the previous form.
        @returns previousForm{Object} API returns the previous form handle.
        @Available Available on all platforms.
        @Usage <pre>function getPreviousForm()
{
    //Get the Previous form
    var previousForm = kony.application.getPreviousForm();
    //Alert the Previous form
    alert("previousForm is::"+previousForm);
}</pre>

getPreviousSessionParams.!doc:
*This API retrieves the session parameters of the previous session in the application life cycle.
@returns listOfParams{Array} Returns a table of the previous session parameters.
@Available Mobile Web
@Usage <pre>//The following function is for getPreviousSessionParams API
function getPreviousSessionParams()
{
Collecting all the params in to an object
var mySessionParams = kony.application.getPreviousSessionParams();
kony.print("mySessionParams are"+mySessionParams);
} </pre>
@Available only on mobile web

getSettingValue.!doc:
This API is used to retrieve current device setting.
@param {String} setting Setting to be queried has to be passed.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Array.<Constants>} args Array of constants to get setting attributes.<b>Optional</b>
@returns {Object} Info of queried setting.
@Available Android, Windows
@usage <pre>
    //Settings that can be retrieved for android: "location", "device_locale", "time_zone", "time", wifi"
    //Settings that can be retrieves for windows: "font", "color", "advancedEffectsEnabled", "inputLanguage"

    //Android
    var locationInfo = kony.application.getSettingValue('location');
    //Windows
    var args= [kony.SystemColorType.Background];
    var colorInfo = kony.application.getSettingValue("color", args);
</pre>

hideAppMenuItems.!doc:
@deprecated This method hides the App Menu items that you specify and shows the rest.
@param {Object} Listofmenuids  Specifies the index number 0<= index <=n-1; where n is the number of App Menu items. <b>Mandatory</b>
@Available All Platforms

invalidateSession.!doc:
This API explicitly invalidates a session on Mobile Web.
@param {Object} formName Specifies the form to which the application must navigate after the session is invalidated.<b>Optional</b>
@param {Function} params Specifies a table of parameters that you want to pass to the new session.<b>Optional</b>
@returns This API navigates to the specified form or remains on the same form if there is no form specified.
@Available Mobile Web
@Usage <pre>
The following function is for invalidateSession API
function invalidateSession()
{
invalidating the session
kony.application.invalidateSession();

}</pre>

openApplicationSettings.!doc:
Opens the application-specific settings or device-level application settings.
@param {Constant} resourceId Specify the resource ID of the resource that you want open its settings. The parameter works only for Windows 10. <b>Optional</b>
@Available Android, iOS, Windows 10
@usage <pre>Kony.application.openApplicationSettings(kony.os.RESOURCE_CONTACTS);</pre>

openMediaURL.!doc:
This API launches the native media player and starts playing the media (audio or video) at the specified URL. The media server provides the appropriate media content depending upon the device (for example, Blackberry, iPhone, etc).
        @param {String} url  Specifies the URL that points to the external web page.<b>Mandatory</b>
        @Usage <pre>function openMediaURL()
{
    //Launching the native media player and starts playing the media (audio or video) at the URL:"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_kKJ_Dmpa7o"
    kony.application.openMediaURL("http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_kKJ_Dmpa7o");
} </pre>

openURLAsync.!doc:
You can use this API, when you want to access an external web page within the application asynchronously. With this API, you can open a web page without using a browser in your application.
   @param {Object} config <b>Mandatory</b>
   @param {String} config.url <b>Mandatory</b>
   @param {Function} config.callback <b>Optional</b>
   @usage <pre>
    var url = "fb://page/" + FB_PAGE_ID;

    var callbackFunction = function(response) {
        if (response == constants.OPEN_URL_SUCCESS) {
            //open url is successful
        } else if (response == constants.OPEN_URL_FAILURE) {
            //failed to open requested url
        } else if (response == constants.OPEN_URL_UNKNOWN) {
            // unknown status on open url
        }
    };

kony.application.openURLAsync({
    url: url,
    callback: callbackFunction
});</pre>

registerForIdleTimeout.!doc:
This API specifies if the application must timeout after a defined period of inactivity (time difference between the current device time and the last time you clicked on any user interface component) and also specifies the action after the timeout interval.
@param {number} timeoutValue The timeout value in minutes. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Function} callback The function that must be executed after the timeout has occurred. The callback function has the logic to display the current form.<b>Mandatory</b>
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>function registerForIdleTimeout()
    {
    kony.application.registerForIdleTimeout(1, test);
    }</pre>

registerMaster.!doc:
This API enables the developer to register new Master.
@param {JSObject} masterConfig An object that contains namespace{String}, classname{String} and name{String}.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns status {Number} A status code is returned indicating the result of the API call.
@Available iOS, Android, Windows, SPA
@Usage <pre>
 kony.application.registerMaster (({ "namespace": "kony.ui", "classname": "IPAddress", "name": "kony.ui.IPAddress" });
</pre>

registerOnSettingsChangeCallback.!doc:
This API is used to listen to the changes in settings. If user wants to stop listening to setting changes after he successfully registered, he has to pass null in second parameter and the list of settings which he want to stop listening has to be passed in first parameter.
@param {Array} settingsList List of settings to listen for has to be provided.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Function} callback Callback to invoke when any setting passed in the 'settingsList' is changed.<b>Mandatory</b>
@Available Android, Windows
@usage <pre>
    function callback(params) {
        //params object has info about the changed setting
    }

    //settingsList supported for android: "location", "device_locale", "time_zone", "time", wifi"
    //settingsList supported for windows: "font", "color", "advancedEffectsEnabled", "inputLanguage"
    kony.application.registerOnSettingsChangeCallback(["location", "device_locale", "time_zone"], callback);
</pre>

removeAppMenuItemAt.!doc:
This API removes the specified App Menu item.
@param {String} appmenuID Appmenu Identifier<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Number} index The index at which the menu item must be removed.<b>Mandatory</b>
@Available All Platforms
@access Write
@usage <pre>
 var appMenuId = "accountMenu";</br>
 //Removing the app menu item at index 2.kony.application.removeAppMenuItemAt(appMenuId,2);</pre>

removeBMState.!doc:
This API removes a specified key from the parameter list of the URL of the form.
    @param {String} formID Identifier of the form for which the parameters of the URL have to be removed. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @param {String} key  A JSON object comprising key value pairs. The key value pairs are user defined. You cannot specify this as a nested structure. i.e the value part cannot be another JSON object. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @Available SPA and Desktop Web
    @usage <pre>kony.application.removeBMState ("form1", "About")
</pre>

removeGestureRecognizer.!doc:
This API allows you to remove the specified gesture recognizer for the specified widget
    @param {function} gestureHandle Specifies the handle to the gesture returned by addGestureRecognizer call.<b>Mandatory</b>
    @Available Available on all platforms except Server Side Mobile Web, BlackBerry 10, Windows 7/Kiosk, and Desktop Web.
    @access Write
    @usage  <pre>Example 1
To remove the TAP gesture recognizer on a flex container with ID flx1 placed on a form frm1, use the following snippet:
frm1.flx1.removeGestureRecognizer( 1 )

Example 2
To remove the SWIPE gesture recognizer on a flex container with ID flx1 placed on a form frm1, use the following snippet:
frm1.flx1.removeGestureRecognizer( 2 )

Example 3
To remove the LONGPRESS gesture recognizer on a flex container with ID hbflx1x1 placed on a form frm1, use the following snippet:
frm1.flx1.removeGestureRecognizer( 3 )</pre>

removeGestureRecognizerForAllForms.!doc:
    @deprecated The "removeGestureRecognizerForAllForms" API is deprecated from 6.0 release. This method allows you to remove a specified gesture recognizer for all Forms. You can remove the gesture recognizer from a Form, Flex Container and a Flex Scroll Container.
    @param {Number} uniqueIdentifier Reference to the gesture. The reference to the gesture is returned by the setGestureRecognizerForAllForms.<b>Mandatory</b>
    @Available Available on all platforms except Server Side Mobile Web, BlackBerry 10, Windows 7/Kiosk,  and Desktop Web.
    @access Write
    @usage  <pre>function callbackClearLongPressGesture()
{
    try{
        kony.application.removeGestureRecognizerForAllForms(uniqueidentifier);
    }
    catch(err){
        alert(typeof err);
        alert("error in function callbackClearLongPressGesture: " + err.message);
    }
}</pre>

