asymmetricDecrypt.!doc:
This API decrypts the input encrypted string.
@param {String} alias  - The alias value generated by using generateAsymmetricKeyPair API.
@param {String} encryptedString  - Mandatory The encrypted string that you must input.
@param {{cipher: String, keysize: String}} propertiesTable [Mandatory] The applicable values for this parameter are cipher algorithm. The relevant value is RSA. And keysize - for specifying either public or private keys.
@return {String} - Returns the decrypted cipher text.
@Available Android, windows 10, Windows Desktop

asymmetricEncrypt.!doc:
This API encrypts the input string and returns the encrypted text.
@param {String} alias  - Optional You can generate the value of the alias parameter by using generateAsymmetricKeyPair API.
@param {String} inputstring  - Optional The input text to be decrypted.
@param {{cipher: String, keysize: String}} propertiesTable - Mandatory The applicable values for this parameter are cipher algorithm. The relevant value is RSA. And keysize - for specifying either public or private keys.
@return {String} - Returns the encrypted cipher text. RSA can only encrypt data to a maximum amount of your keysize(256bytes) – padding/header data.
@Available Android, windows 10, Windows Desktop

createHMacHash.!doc:
This function generates a hash-based message authentication code (HMAC) that verifies the data integrity and authenticity of the data.
@param {String} algo -A string that contain the hashing algorithm. See the Remarks section below for more information.
@param {String} key -A string that holds the input key for the algorithm.
@param {String} message -A string that contains the plain text message for which the hash is generated.
@return {String} - hexadecimal string that holds the hash value created using the specified algorithm for the given input string.
@throws {Exception}
@Available iOS and Android.

createHash.!doc:
Hash value is a unique and compact numerical representation of a chunk of data. This API provides the ability to create a hash value in hexadecimal format for a given input string using the specified algorithm.
@param {String} algo  Algorithm to be used for creating the hash value. Possible values are: sha1, sha224, sha256, sha384, sha512, md2, md4, and md5 <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {String} inputstring  It is Input string for which the hash value needs to be created. <b>Mandatory</b>
@returns {String} Hash value created using the specified algorithm for the given input string. This string is in hexadecimal format. Length of the hashValue string in bytes is as follows (for each algorithm):1. sha1 2. sha224 3. sha256 4. sha384 5. sha512 6. md2 7. md4 8. md5
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>var algo="sha1";
    var inputstr="pleasecreatehash";
    var myHashValue = kony.crypto.createHash(algo,inputstr);</pre>

createPBKDF2Key.!doc:
This function creates a Password-Based Key Derivation Function 2(PBKDF2) key for protecting passwords and other similar tasks.
@param {String} algo  - A string that specifies the hashing algorithm used for creating the key. For a list of supported algorithms by platform, see the Kony API documentation.
@param {String} password  - A string that contains the master password from which a derived key is generated.
@param {String} salt  - A string that holds a random salt input string from a programmer
@param {Number} iteration  - A number that specifies the desired number of iterations. Should be at least 10,000 as per NIST standards.
@param {Number} klen  - An optional numeric parameter that specifies the desired length of the derived key in bits. If the key length is not specified, this value defaults to 256-bits.
@return {String} - Returns the key created using the PBKDF2 algorithm.
@throws {Exception}
@Available iOS, Android and Windows

decrypt.!doc:
This API provides the ability to decrypt the encrypted text with the specified key and algorithm. The API returns the decrypted text.
@param {String} algo  Algorithm using which the encrypted text needs to be decrypted. <b>Mandatory</b> Possible values are: aes and tripledes
@param {Object} generatedkey  An object that holds the key to be used for decryption. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Object} encryptedRawbytes  An object that contains the rawbytes of the encrypted text to be decrypted. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {JS Object} propertiesTable  - <b>Mandatory</b>A JavaScript object that contains key-value pairs necessary for decryption. For details, see the Remarks section below.
@returns {String} The clear text decrypted from the encrypted rawbytes.
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>var algo="aes";
    var aeskey=
    kony.crypto.
    newKey("
    passphrase",128,{passphrasetext:"inputstring1",subalgo:"aes",passphrasehashalgo:"var inputstr="encryptedtextrawbytes";
    var prptobj={padding:"pkcs5",mode:"cbc",initializationvector: "1234567890123456"};
    myClearText = kony.crypto.decrypt(algo,aeskey,inputstr,prptobj);</pre>

deleteKey.!doc:
Thid API provides you the ability to delete the key from the device store if you are sure that you do not need that key anymore in the application.
@param {String} uniqueID Unique ID represents the key on the device store (this is the ID returned by kony.crypto.saveKey API). <b>Mandatory</b>
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>EncryptDecryptKey = kony.crypto.newKey("passphrase", 128,
{passphrasetext={"inputstring1"}, subalgo="aes",
passphrasehashalgo="md5"});
myUniqueIDKey = kony.crypto.saveKey("myKey",EncryptDecryptKey);
kony.crypto.deleteKey(myUniqueIDKey);</pre>

encrypt.!doc:
This API provides the ability to encrypt the input text with the specified key and algorithm. The rawbytes of the encrypted text are returned.
@param {String} algo  Algorithm using the input string that needs to be encrypted. <b>Mandatory</b> Possible values are: 1. aes 2. tripledes 3. rsa
@param {Object} generatedkey  The key to be used for encryption. <b>Mandatory</b> Note: This API accepts only the key generated using the kony.crypto.newKey API.
@param {String} inputstring  - Data which needs to be encrypted. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Object} propertiesTable  - This Object contains the following key-value pairs: padding - a string that denotes the padding that needs to be applied. mode - a string that denotes the encryption mode. initializationvector - a string that denotes the IV to be used. Mandatory
@returns {Object} – userdata The rawbytes for the encrypted version of the input text.
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>var algo="aes";
    =>var aeskey=
    kony.crypto.
    newKey("
    passphrase",128,{passphrasetext:"inputstring1",subalgo:"aes",passphrasehashalgo:"=>var inputstr="pleaseencryptme";
    =>var
    prptobj={padding:"
    pkcs5",mode:"cbc",initializationvector:"1234567890123456"};
    =>var myEncryptedText =
    kony.crypto.encrypt(algo,aeskey,inputstr,prptobj);</pre>

generateAsymmetricKeyPair.!doc:
This API is used to generate public and private keys for encryption and decryption processes. Typically, you can use the Public key to verify the digital signature and plain text data, whereas you can use the Private key to create a digital signature and to decrypt the text.
@param {Object} propertiesTable  - (Mandatory) A key-value pair that you can use to generate asymmetric key pairs.
@param {String} propertiesTable.alias  -(Mandatory) UTF-8 string.
@param {Number} propertiesTable.keysize  - Size of the key that is generated by using this API.
@param {String} propertiesTable.cipher  - Use cipher algorithm. The applicable value is RSA.
@param {Number} propertiesTable.Publicexponent  - An odd integer. The recommended value is 65337.
@param {byte} propertiesTable.Padding  - For RSA algorithm, the possible padding modes are PKCS1, OAEP and None. The recommended value is OAEP. The maximum byte lengths for the padding input value are: PKCS1: < b-11, OAEP: < b-41, None: < b
@param {String} propertiesTable.Mode  - Block mode. The possible values are ECB and None.
@param {String} propertiesTable.Digest  - The hash algorithm to be used. The possible values are SHA-1, SHA-256, SHA-224, SHA-384 and SHA-512.
@return {Boolean} - Status of the key value generation.
@Available Android, Windows10, WindowsDesktop

generateSecureRandom.!doc:
This API is used to generate cryptographically secure random numbers.
@param {Object} propertiesTable  - (Mandatory) A key-value pair that you can use to send the type and size of the key, in order to generate secure random cryptographic numbers
@param {String} propertiesTable.type - The possible values for the type key are 'bytes' and 'Base64'.
@param {Number} propertiesTable.size - The length of the generated randomkey.
@return {Object} - Secure random key of the bytes array or Base64 string of the specified length.
@Available Android, iOS, Windows10, WindowsDesktop

newKey.!doc:
This API allows you to create a key for cryptography using the specified algorithm. The key created using this API is used for encrypting clear text and decrypting the encrypted data.
@param {String} algo  Scheme using which the key is to be created. Possible values are: securerandom - uses a secure random number as the scheme to generate an unique key. random - uses a random number as the scheme to generate an unique key. passphrase - for this scheme, you need to pass the exact passphrase using which the key needs to be generated. The passphrase scheme always produces the same key for the same passphrase text. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Number} keystrength  Is number of bits that indicate the key strength. For the aes subalgo - possible values are 128, 192, 256. For the tripledes subalgo - possible values are 192. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Object} propertiesTable  passphrasetext {Array of Strings}- the exact passphrase using which the key needs to be generated if the scheme is passphrase. passphrasetext is a string of array that contains strings(//repeated text with same meaning). For subalgo aes, it contains a single string (passphrasetext = {"inputstring1"}), whereas for tripledes subalgo, it contains three strings (passphrasetext = {"inputstring1","inputstring2","inputstring3"}). passphrasehashlogo - hashing algorithm to be applied for the passphrase text. (applicable only on iPhone).Possible values for the hash algorithm are: o md2,md4, and md5 for key strength of 128 and sha2 for key strength of 256 <b>Mandatory</b>
@returns userdata {Object} The key that is created using the specified algorithm.
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>var myEncryptionKey = kony.crypto.newKey("random",128,{subalgo="aes"});</pre>

readKey.!doc:
This API provides you the ability to read the key from the device store.
@param {String} uniqueID Unique ID represents the key on the device store (this is the ID returned by kony.crypto.saveKey API). <b>Mandatory</b>
@returns {rawbytes} – Object This key is generated using aes, tripledes, or RSA algorithms and saved on the device store.
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>var EncryptDecryptKey = kony.crypto.newKey("passphrase", 128,
    {passphrasetext={"inputstring1"}, subalgo="aes",
    passphrasehashalgo="md5"});
    myUniqueIDKey = kony.crypto.saveKey("myKey",EncryptDecryptKey);
    var myCryptoKey = kony.crypto.readKey(myUniqueIDKey);
    myCryptoKey will hold the same key as EncryptDecryptKey</pre>

retrieveAsymmetricPublicKey.!doc:
This API returns the Public key for the alias that you provide.
@param {String} alias -The alias value generated by using generateAsymmetricKeyPair API.
@return {String} - Public part of the asymmetric key-pair for the provided alias.
@Available Android, Windows10, WindowsDesktop

retrievePublicKey.!doc:
This API provides the ability to extract the public key from a base64 string of encoded X509 certificate or a locally packaged X509 certificate.
@param {String} algo The algorithm used for the public key. Possible value is: RSA <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {String} inputsource This parameter indicates the name of the Input source certificate from which the key needs to retrieved. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {boolean} islocalresource This flag defines how the inputsource string needs to be interpreted. <b>Mandatory</b> a. islocalresource is false - represents that the input source is base64 string of X509 certificate. b. islocalresource is true - represents that the input source is name of the local resource for the certificate. For example, public.cer.
@returns userdata {Object} The public key extracted from the certificate.
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>var myKey = kony.crypto.retrievePublicKey("rsa","public.cer",true);</pre>

saveKey.!doc:
This API allows you to save the generated key on the device store. If a key does not exist with the given name, the API creates a key; if a key exists with the given name, the API updates the same. The key is saved and a unique identifier is returned.
@param {String} nameUnique name with which you want to save the key on the device store. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Object} key The key that you want to save on the device. <b>Mandatory</b>
@returns {String} The unique ID represents the saved key on the device store. we can access the key from the device store using this unique ID.
@Available All Platforms
@usage <pre>myuniqueID = kony.crypto.saveKey("myKey",EncryptDecryptKey);</pre>

executeSql.!doc:
This API allows you to execute a specified SQL statement on the given database. This is an asynchronous API.
        @param {String} transactionId  Specifies the unique ID of the transaction. <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {String} SQLStatement  Specifies the SQL statement that must be executed. <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {Object} arg Specifies the arguments for executing the SQL statement. If this parameter is not specified or is nil, then the statement is executed without any arguments.
        @param {Function} SQLStatementSuccessCallback  Specifies the callback function that must be executed when the execution of the SQL statement is a success. <b>Optional</b>
        @param {Function} SQLStatementErrorCallback Specifies the callback function that must be executed when the execution of the SQL statement is a failure. <b>Optional</b>
        @Available iPhone,Android, BB,SPA,iPad
        @usage <pre>var dbName="konytestDB";<br/>
var version="1.0";<br/>
var displayName="demo web SQL Database";<br/>
var estimatedSize=5*1024*1024;<br/>
//5*1024*1024 indicates 5 MB<br/>
var databaseObjectId = kony.db.openDatabase(dbName,version, displayname, estimatedSize);<br/>
//databaseObjectId contains the unique ID of the database<br/>
 function sql_success(transactionId, resultset)<br/>
{
    //logic to process the resultset<br/>
}
 function sql_errorcallback(err)<br/>
{
    print("Error processing sql statement error code=" + err["code"]);<br/>
}
 function myTransactionCallback(dbId)<br/>
{
    //SQLTransaction contains implementation of executeSql method<br/>
    // invoke kony.db.executesql method for sql trasaction<br/>
    var sqlStatement = "SELECT FROM employee";<br/>
    kony.db.executeSql(dbId, sqlStatement, null, sql_success, sql_errorcallback);<br/>
}

function myTransactionErrorCallback(SQLError)<br/>
{
    // proceed with the logic<br/>
}

function mySuccessCallback()<br/>
{
    // proceed with the logic<br/>
}
kony.db.transaction(databaseObjectId, myTransactionCallback, myTransactionErrorCallback, mySuccessCallback);</pre>

openDatabase.!doc:
This API allows you to open the specified version of a particular database. This is an asynchronous APIs.
        @param {String} name Specifies the actual name of the database that you want to open. <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {String} version Specifies the version of the database that you want to open. <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {String} displayName  Specifies the display name of the database that you want to open. <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {Number} estimatedsize Specifies the approximate size of the database in bytes. Applicable on SPA. <b>Optional</b>
        @returns    {String}    Returns the unique ID of the database
        @Available iPhone,Android, BB, MobileWeb advanced, SPA,iPad
        @usage <pre>var dbName="konytestDB";<br/>
var version="1.0";<br/>
var displayName="demo web SQL Database";<br/>
var estimatedSize=5*1024*1024;<br/>
//5*1024*1024 indicates 5 MB<br/>
var databaseObjectId = kony.db.openDatabase(dbName,version, displayname, estimatedSize);<br/>
databaseObjectId contains the unique ID of the database</pre>

readTransaction.!doc:
This API allows you to read a specified transaction. This API creates a SQLTransaction object for read-only transactions.
        @param {String} dbaseObjectId Specifies the unique ID of the database <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {Function} TransactionCallback Specifies the callback function that contains the transactions. <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {Function} TransactionErrorCallback Specifies the callback that must be executed if there is an error in executing the transaction. This callback function is used to roll back the updates to the database. <b>Optional</b>
        @param {Function} SuccessCallback Specifies the callback that must be executed if the transaction is successful. <b>Optional</b>
        @Available iPhone,Android, BB,SPA,iPad
        @usage <pre>var dbName="konytestDB";<br/>
var version="1.0";<br/>
var displayName="demo web SQL Database";<br/>
var estimatedSize=5*1024*1024;<br/>
//5*1024*1024 indicates 5 MB<br/>
var databaseObjectId = kony.db.openDatabase(dbName,version, displayname, estimatedSize);<br/>
//databaseObjectId contains the unique ID of the database<br/>
function myTransactionCallback(dbId)<br/>
{
    //SQLTransaction contains implementation of executeSql method   <br/>
    // invoke kony.db.executesql method for sql trasaction<br/>
}
function myTransactionErrorCallback(SQLError) <br/>
{
    // proceed with the logic<br/>
}
function mySuccessCallback()<br/>
{
    // proceed with the logic <br/>
}
kony.db.readTransaction(databaseObjectId, myTransactionCallback, myTransactionErrorCallback, mySuccessCallback);</pre>

sqlResultsetRowItem.!doc:
This API returns the row available at the specified index. If there is no such row, then the API returns nil.
        @param {String} transactionID Specifies the unique ID of the transaction. <b> Mandatory</b>
        @param {Array.<objects>} SQLResultSet Specifies the name of the SQL result set. <b> Mandatory</b>
        @param {number} index Specifies the index from which the row is to be retrieved. <b> Mandatory</b>
        @returns {String|Null} <ul><li>Returns the row item at the specified index</li><li>Returns null if there is no row available at the specified index.</li></ul>
        @usage <pre>function sql_success(transactionId, resultset)<br/>
{
//logic to process the resultset<br/>
for (var i=0; i<resultset.length;i++)<br/>
{
    var rowItem = Kony.db.sqlResultsetRowItem(transactionId,resultset,i);<br/>
    print("empID:" + rowItem["empID"] + " empName:" + rowItem["empName"] + " depID:" + rowItem["depName"]);<br/>
}
}</pre>

transaction.!doc:
This API allows you to execute the specified transaction on the given database. When you invoke this API, it returns immediately and asynchronously executes the transaction.
        @param {String} dbaseObjectId Specifies the unique ID of the database <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {Function} TransactionCallback  Specifies the callback function that contains the transactions. <b>Mandatory</b>
        @param {Function} TransactionErrorCallback Specifies the callback that must be executed if there is an error in executing the transaction. This callback function is used to roll back the updates to the database. <b>Optional</b>
        @param {Function} SuccessCallback  Specifies the callback that must be executed if the transaction is successful. <b>Optional</b>
        @Available iPhone,Android, BB,SPA,iPad
        @usage <pre>var dbName="konytestDB";<br/>
var version="1.0";<br/>
var displayName="demo web SQL Database";<br/>
var estimatedSize=5*1024*1024;<br/>
//5*1024*1024 indicates 5 MB<br/>
var databaseObjectId = kony.db.openDatabase(dbName,version, displayname, estimatedSize);<br/>
//databaseObjectId contains the unique ID of the database<br/>
function myTransactionCallback(dbId)<br/>
{
    //SQLTransaction contains implementation of executeSql method<br/>
    // invoke kony.db.executesql method for sql trasaction  <br/>
}
function myTransactionErrorCallback(SQLError)   <br/>
{
    // proceed with the logic<br/>
}
function mySuccessCallback() <br/>
{
// proceed with the logic<br/>
}
kony.db.transaction(databaseObjectId, myTransactionCallback, myTransactionErrorCallback, mySuccessCallback);</pre>

disableQuickActionItems.!doc:
This API disables pinned shortcuts that were previously enabled. If the target shortcuts are already disabled, this method does nothing.
It sets mentioned disabled message to all action items . On trying to launch disabled shortcut actionItem toast message  is shown to user. This method should strictly used for dynamic shortcut Action Items .
Please take care not to call the method with static quickAction Ids
@param {Object} quickActionList An object of quickAction id
@param {String} disableMessage Specifies the disableMessage
@returns Void

enableQuickActionItems.!doc:
This API helps to re-enable pinned shortcuts that were previously disabled. If the target shortcuts are already enabled, this method does nothing.
@param {Array} quickActionId An array of quickAction id
@returns Void

getQuickActionItems.!doc:
This API provides a way to get an array dynamic Quick Action Items that are already set to the app if any.
Note: The returned dynamic quick action items wouldn't have icon key-value pair.
@returns {Array} Returns an array of dynamic Quick Action items if any are set to the app. Otherwise, it returns an empty array.
@usage <pre>
    try {

      var quickActionItems = kony.forcetouch.getQuickActionItems();
      alert(JSON.stringify(quickActionItems));

    } catch (args) {
      alert(args.toString());
    }
</pre>

setQuickActionItems.!doc:
This API allows to set dynamic Quick Action Items to the app.
Note : To localize the title, sub title for a Home screen dynamic quick action, employ the kony internalization API’s.
@param {Array} quickActionItems - Mandatory, Array of Quick Action items
@return {Boolean} true if atleast one action is added successfully. Otherwise, it returns false
@usage <pre>
    [{
      "id": "com.kony.first",
      "title": "firstPage",
      "subtitle": "takes to first page",
      "icon": kony.forcetouch.QUICK_ACTION_ICON_TYPE_COMPOSE,
      "info": {
          "feed": "feed to first form"
      }
   },
      {
      "id": "com.kony.second",
      "title": "secondPage",
      "subtitle": "takes to second page",
      "icon": kony.forcetouch.QUICK_ACTION_ICON_TYPE_HOME,
      "info": {
          "feed": "feed to second form"
      }
   }]
</pre>

getError.!doc:
This API uses the handle to the error object and returns the actual error object.
        @param {Object|Handle} error The input parameters of this API is either the Original Error object or a handle received in try/catch block.<b>Mandatory</b>
        @returns {Object}   Returns the JS error object.
        @Available All Platforms
        @usage <pre>try

{

….

}

catch ( e )

{

var err = kony.getError(e);

if (err instanceof KonyError)

alert(“A Kony error”);

else (err instanceof EvalError)

alert(“A JS Eval Eror”);

}</pre>

executeFunctionInNativeContext.!doc:
This API provides the ability to send data from the browser widget execution context to native context.
   @param {String} Function Specifies the function that needs to be executed<b>Mandatory</b>
   @param {Object} paramsTable Specifies the list of parameters that the user defined function expects as input parameters.
   @Available iPhone and Android
   @access Write
   @usage <pre>
    //Defining executeFunctionInNativeContext
function executeFunctionInNativeContext()
{
    kony.hybrid.executeFunctionInNativeContext("JSFunThree",
{"KonySolutions",false,{"abc","xyz"}});

}</pre>

executeFunctionInSPAContext.!doc:
This API provides the ability to send data from the native execution context to browser widget context.
   @param {String} Function Specifies the function that needs to be executed<b>Mandatory</b>
   @param {Object} paramsTable Specifies the list of parameters that the user defined function expects as input parameters.
   @Available iPhone and Android
   @access Write
   @usage <pre>
    function executeFunctionInSPAContext()
{

    kony.hybrid.executeFunctionInSPAContext("JSFunThree",["KonyLabs",2012,false]);</pre>
}

