createImage.!doc:
Creates an Image. This function has three overloads.
 The param could be image as RawBytes or a bundledImageFileName or an Image widget.
@param {Object} A RawBytes object containing the image's bitmap.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns This function returns an image object with its associated bitmap.
@Available Available on all platforms.
@access Write

createImageFromSnapShot.!doc:
Creates an Image by taking a snapshot of a widget.
@param {Object} widget The widget that this function takes a snapshot of. The snapshot is used for the bitmap of the Image created by the function.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns This function returns an Image that contains a snapshot of the widget passed in through the widget parameter.
@Available Available on all platforms.
@access Write

cropImageInTiles.!doc:
Crops the bitmap in an Image object and returns it as an array of tiles.
@param {Object} image The Image widget containing the bitmap to be cropped.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Number} xTiles The number of equally-sized tiles that can be created in the x direction.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Number} yTiles The number of equally-sized tiles that can be created in the y direction.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns This function returns an array of Image widgets that were created from tiles of the bitmap in the Image widget in the image parameter.
@Available Available on all platforms.
@access Write

cropImageInTilesForRects.!doc:
Crops portions of an Image widget's bitmap to a set of rectangles and returns an array of Image widgets containing the cropped bitmaps.
@param image An Image widget containing the bitmap to be cropped.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Array} rects An array of rectangles specified as the (x,y) coordinates of the upper left corner and the height and width of the rectangle. Format: [ [x,y,w,h],[x1,y1,w1,h1],... ]<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns This function returns an array of Image widgets that contain the bitmap information from the bitmap in the Image widget passed through the image parameter.
@Available Available on all platforms.
@access Write

findImageInGallery.!doc:
 Finds image within a gallery. Note1: In case of IOS,  this api searches the image in the Gallery with the imageName is a unique identifier. Note2: In case of Android & Windows If album name is provided it will search for the given file in the specific album, if not it will search in Pictures gallery. Hence album name is not mandatory.
@param {Object} config - Mandatory, config is a mandatory argument which is a dictionary with configurable properties.
@param {String} config.albumName - optional, A String containing the album name to search for the specified image exist or not. Note:  In case of IOS, image names are uniqueidentifiers to identify the image, this argument will be ignored.
@throws Error if the value of the albumName key is not of the string type, throw the exception with errorcode as 100 with the message "Invalid argument".
@param {String} config.imageName - Mandatory, A string containing the file name with the extension of the bitmap to use for the image.
@throws Error: if the value of the imageName key is not of the string type, throw the exception with errorcode as 100 with the message "Invalid argument".
@returns {kony.types.RawBytes} - This api return RawBytes of image if exist or null, doesn't exist.

copyTo.!doc:
Copies a file to the given destination path.
@param {String} Path  path to the destination directory.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {String} newName  New name of the file/directory.<b>Optional</b>
@returns {Null}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

createDirectory.!doc:
Creates a directory on the file system represented by this file object.
@returns {Boolean}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

createFile.!doc:
Creates a file on the file system represented by this file object.
@returns {Boolean}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

exists.!doc:
The exist API checks, if the file or directory exists on the file system represented by this file object.
@returns {Boolean}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

getFilesList.!doc:
The getFilesList API returns kony.io.FileList object representing the files and directories available under this file object directory.
@returns kony.io.FileList{Object} FileList object or null if this File is not identified as a directory.
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

isDirectory.!doc:
The isDirectory API checks, if this object represents a directory file on the file system.
@returns {Boolean}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

isFile.!doc:
The isFile API checks, if this object represents a typical file on the file system but not a directory.
@returns {Boolean}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

moveTo.!doc:
Moves a file to the given destination path.
@param {String} Path  path to the destination directory.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {String} newName  New name of the file/directory.<b>Optional</b>
@returns {Null}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

read.!doc:
The read API returns the kony.types.RawBytes of this file.
@returns kony.types.RawBytes{RawBytes} Rawbytes representing the content of the file. Returns null in case of non existent file.
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

readAsText.!doc:
The readAsText API returns the data as text represented by this rawBytes . Returns null if this represents a binary.
@param {Index} Index in the FileList.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns {String} Text available in this rawbytes.
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

remove.!doc:
Deletes a file or a directory.
@param {Boolean} boolean True-deletes the folder and all its content recursively, False-if the directory is empty it shall be removed.
@param {Boolean} deleteRecursive Ignored in case of a file.<b>Optional</b>
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

rename.!doc:
Renames a file or a directory
@param {String} newName  New name for the file/directory.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns {Boolean}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

write.!doc:
The write API writes the given content into the file.
@param {Rawbytes|string} data Data to write of type text string or kony.types.RawBytes.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Boolean} Append True to append the data. Default is false, that means overrides the content.
@returns {Boolean}
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

item.!doc:
The item API returns the File object at the specified index in the FileList.
@param {number} index  Index in the FileList.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns File{Object} File object at specified index. Null if there is no File at specified index or if index is not in FileList range.
@Available  iOS, Android, and Windows platforms

browse.!doc:
This API provides the ability to browse and select files from your local system.
    @param {String} browseConfig  Configuration params which is a simple JSON object of key value pairs, that drive the possible options during the browse. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @param {Object} browseCallBack The callback is executed once the user closes the browse dialog. As part of call back, the platform provides the list of files that have been selected as an array of kony.io.FileSystem objects. The call back signature is as follows: browseCallBack (event, FileList[]). <b>Mandatory</b>
    @returns {Null}
    @Available Desktop Web
    @usage <pre>
    var config = {
        selectMultipleFiles: true,
        filter: ["image/png", "image/jpeg"]
    };
    var selectedFileCallback = function(event, filelist) {
      //logic to iterate filelist
    };
   kony.io.FileSystem.browse(config, selectedFileCallback);
</pre>

copyBundledRawFileTo.!doc:
Copies a bundled file from the application binary to the specified destination path on the device.
    @param {String} rawFileName  specify the file name with the extension of a pre-bundled raw file that you want to copy. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @param {String} destFilePath  specify the absolute file path along with the file name and extension (if any) where you want to copy the pre-bundled file. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @Available Android, iOS, Windows
    @usage <pre>//The destination file name can be different from the source.
try {
    var destFilePath = kony.io.FileSystem.getDataDirectoryPath()+"/Destinationfile.pdf";
    var destFile = new kony.io.File(destFilePath);
    //copyBundledRawFileTo API overrides the destination file with new one.
    //Hence check before copying
    if(!destFile.exists()) {
      var fileObj = kony.io.FileSystem.copyBundledRawFileTo(“Sourcefile.pdf”, destFilePath);
    } else {
      kony.print("File is already available");
    }
} catch(e) {
    kony.print(“Exception “+e);
}</pre>

getDatabaseDirectoryPath.!doc:
Returns the application's database directory path (from application's private file system) where kony.db APIs access the database files.
    @returns Application's database directory path in the form of String.
    @Available Android, iOS, Windows
    @usage <pre>//Example for opening the pre-bundled database
var fileObj = null;
try {
    var destFilePath = kony.io.FileSystem.getDatabaseDirectoryPath()+”test.db”;
    var destFile = new kony.io.File(destFilePath);
    //copyBundledRawFileTo API overrides the destination file with new one.
    //Hence check before copying
    if(!destFile.exists()) {
      fileObj = kony.io.FileSystem.copyBundledRawFileTo(dbName, destFilePath);
    } else {
      fileObj = destFile;
      kony.print("File is already available");
    }
} catch(e) {
    kony.print(“Exception “+e);
  }
  if(fileObj == null) {
    kony.print(“Copy failed”);
  } else {
    kony.print(“Copy Success”);
  }
var dbObject = kony.db.openDatabase("test.db", "1.0", "Prebundled SQL Database", 5 * 1024 * 1024);
</pre>

uploadFiles.!doc:
When the developer invokes this API with the list of files, the  internally iterates through the fileList and makes the network call to the URL mentioned and uploads the files. The  assumes that the application using this API has the necessary server side infrastructure to handle the upload.
    @param {String} URL Provide target location to upload the file. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @param {Object} fileList Specifies the list of files to be uploaded. This is as an array of kony.io.FileSystem.file objects. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @param {Object} uploadConfig Configuration parameters, which is a simple JSON object of key value pairs, that provides the possible options during the upload. Currently there are no keys. <b>Mandatory</b>
    @param {Object} uploadCallBack The callback is invoked each time when the file is getting uploaded. The signature of the callback is as follows: uploadCallBack(URL, uploadStates). <b>Mandatory</b>
    upLoadState [Object] - Mandatory This is an array of key value map states of the individual files that are uploaded. The key value map currently consists of the following keys:
    file: File (kony.io.FileSystem.file) object
     status: One of the following four status are possible :
     FILE_UPLOAD_START_STATE = 0
     FILE_UPLOAD_PROGRESS_STATE = 1
     FILE_UPLOAD_COMPLETE_STATE = 2
     FILE_UPLOAD_ERROR_STATE = 3
     uploadBytes: Number of bytes that are uploaded.


    @returns {Null}
    @Available Desktop Web
    @usage <pre>function UploadBtn_onClick_seq0() { // Event on upload button click
    var uploadURL = “http://10.10.4.17:8080/fileupload/upload”;
    var filesQueue = [fileObject1, fileObject2]; //Array of File objects got in browse callback.
    var uploadCallback = function(url, uploadState) {
        //logic to process upload state
    };
   kony.io.FileSystem.uploadFiles(uploadURL, filesQueue, uploadCallBack);
 };
</pre>

remove.!doc:
Delete secure data from the keychain with the provided identifier.
@param {Object} dictionary A Dictionary containing the identifier(identifier) (string). Identifier is required to uniquely identify the secure data.
@returns {Array} Array containing the status code.
@Available iOs
@usage <pre>var cred = {"identifier":"Apple"};<br/>
kony.keychain.remove(cred);
</pre>

retrieve.!doc:
Retrieve secure data from the keychain with the provided identifier.
@param {Object} dictionary A Dictionary containing the identifier(identifier) (string). Identifier is required to uniquely identify the secure data.
@returns dictionary{Object} Dictionary containing the resulting secure data, account name, and the identifier (both string).
@Available iOs
@usage <pre>var cred = {"identifier":"Apple"};<br/>
kony.keychain.retrieve(cred);
</pre>

save.!doc:
Save provided secure data to the keychain.
@param {Object} dictionary A Dictionary of identifier(identifier), account name(secureaccount), and secure data(securedata) (all strings). Identifier and account name is required to uniquely identify the data.
@returns {Number|Object} Error numbers, Error dictionary with errors identifying with account or password.
@Available iOs
@usage <pre>var cred = {"securedata":"Appleseed", "secureaccount":"John","identifier":"Apple"};<br/>
kony.keychain.save(cred);
</pre>

authenticate.!doc:
The API is used to authenticate the user.
     @param {Constant} authenticationMode Specifies the authentication mode for which the status is requested. <b>Mandatory</b>
     @param {Function} statusCallback A callback conveys the status of the authentication with appropriate status and message. <b>Mandatory</b>
     @param {JSObject} configMap Specifies the configuration dictionary for the specified authentication mode. <b>Mandatory</b>
     @Available Android and iOS
     @usage <pre>function statusCB(status,message)
{
  If(status == 5000)
   {
     kony.ui.Alert({message: "AUTHENTICATION SUCCESSFULL", alertType: constants.ALERT_TYPE_INFO, yesLabel:"Close"}, {});
   }
  else
   {
     var messg = status+message;
     kony.ui.Alert({message: messg, alertType: constants.ALERT_TYPE_INFO, yesLabel:"Close"}, {});
   }
}
function authUsingTouchID()
{
  var config = {"promptMessage" : "PLEASE AUTHENTICATE USING YOUR TOUCH ID"};
  kony.localAuthentication.authenticate(constants.LOCAL_AUTHENTICATION_MODE_TOUCH_ID,statusCB,config);
}</pre>

cancelAuthentication.!doc:
The API cancels the current authentication process.
    @returns status {Number} The 5002 status code is returned indicating the authentication is cancelled.
    @Available Android
    @usage <pre>var cancelButton = kony.ui.Button({onClick: btnOnClick});
funtction btnOnClick () {
kony.localAuthentication.cancelAuthentication()
}</pre>

getBiometryType.!doc:
The API differentiates whether a device supports either the Touch ID or Face ID feature.
    @Available iOS
    @usage <pre>
    function getMessageForLocalAuth() {
        var promptMessage = "Sign in with ";
        switch (kony.localAuthentication.getBiometryType()) {
            case constants.BIOMETRY_TYPE_NONE:
                // Handle the case if the device doesn't support any biometryType
                break;
            case constants.BIOMETRY_TYPE_TOUCHID:
                promptMessage += "TouchID";
                break;
            case constants.BIOMETRY_TYPE_FACEID:
                promptMessage += "FaceID";
                break;
            case constants.BIOMETRY_TYPE_UNDEFINED:
                // Handle the case if the device is not a iOS11 device or later
                break;
        }
            return promptMessage;
    }
</pre>

getStatusForAuthenticationMode.!doc:
The API returns the status of the authentication mode.
     @param {Constant} authenticationMode Specifies the authentication mode for which the status is requested. <b>Mandatory</b>
	@returns status {Number} A status code is returned indicating the support for local authentication using Touch ID.
	@Available Android and iOS
     @usage <pre>function isAuthUsingTouchSupported()
{
  var status = kony.localAuthentication.getStatusForAuthenticationMode(constants.LOCAL_AUTHENTICATION_ODE_TOUCH_ID);
  if(status == 5000)
   {
     kony.ui.Alert({message: "AUTHENTICATION BY TOUCHID SUPPORTED", alertType: constants.ALERT_TYPE_INFO, yesLabel:"Close"}, {});
   }
  else
   {
     var msg = "TOUCHID AUTHENTICATION RETURNED THE STATUS ::"+status;
     kony.ui.Alert({message: status, alertType: constants.ALERT_TYPE_INFO, yesLabel:"Close"}, {});
   }
}</pre>

clearWatch.!doc:
When invoked, it must first check the value of the given watchID argument.
@param {Number} watchID Specifies number that uniquely identifies the watch. <b>Mandatory</b>
@Available All platforms.
@usage <pre>kony.location.clearWatch(watchID);</pre>

getCurrentPosition.!doc:
When invoked it must immediately return and then asynchronously attempt to obtain the current location of the device.
     @param {Function} successcallback Specifies the callback function that must be executed when the API call is successful. The signature of the callback function is successcallback(position) where position contains the coordinates of the geolocation that are created and returned by the API. <b>Mandatory</b>
     @param {Function} errorcallback Specifies the callback function that must be executed when the API call fails. <b>Optional</b>
     @param {Object} positionoptions Using this parameter, the user can customize the retrieval of the geolocation. <b>Optional</b>
     @param {Number} positionoptions.accuracyMode	Specifies the accuracy and power requirements to be met while fetching the device location
     @param {Boolean} positionoptions.getActiveLocation	Set to true to get the current location fix on the device. When you use this property, active location computation is caused in the device. This property returns a single fresh location if the device location can be determined within a reasonable time period (tens of seconds). If the device location is not determined within a reasonable time period, the property returns a Null value.
     @param {Boolean} positionoptions.enableHighAccuracy	Provides a hint to the implementation in order to receive the best possible result.
     @param {Number} positionoptions.maximumAge 	Indicates the application to accept a cached position whose age is no greater than the specified time in milliseconds.
     @param {Number} positionoptions.minimumTime 	Indicates the desired interval for active location updates in milliseconds.
     @param {Boolean} positionoptions.requestModifyLocationSettings	When you set this parameter to true, if the app cannot fetch the device location due to inadequate location settings on the device, the system automatically invokes a dialog box that helps the user enable the necessary location settings with a single tap.
     @param {Boolean} positionoptions.requireBackgroundAccess	Set to true to fetch the device location updates even when the app is running in the background.
     @param {Number}  positionoptions.timeout	Denotes the maximum length of time in milliseconds that is allowed to pass from the call.
     @param {Boolean} positionoptions.useBestProvider	Set to true to improve the reliability of calls to this function on Android devices. Omitting this option on Android could cause calls to this function to have intermittent timeouts.

     @Available Available on all platforms except Windows 7 Kiosk and prior to IE8 releases.
     @usage
        <pre>function successcallback(position)<br/>
{
    var geoPosition = "Latitude: " + position.coords.latitude;
    geoPosition = geoPosition + " Longitude: " + position.coords.longitude;
    geoPosition = geoPosition + " Altitude: " + position.coords.altitude;
    geoPosition = geoPosition + " Accuracy: " + position.coords.accuracy;
    geoPosition = geoPosition + " Altitude Accuracy: "+ position.coords.altitudeAccuracy;
    geoPosition = geoPosition + " Heading: " + position.coords.heading;
    geoPosition = geoPosition + " Speeding: " + position.coords.speeding;
    geoPosition = geoPosition + " Timestamp: " + position.timestamp;
    alert(geoPosition);
}
function errorcallback(positionerror)<br/>
{
    var errorMesg = "Error code: " + positionerror.code;
    errorMesg = errorMesg  + " message: " + positionerror.message;
    alert(errorMesg);

}

var positionoptions = {maximumage: 3000};<br/>
// Options: retrieve the location every 3 seconds<br/>
kony.location.getCurrentPosition(successcallback, errorcallback, positionoptions);<br/>

</pre>

