containsLocation.!doc:
This function tests to see whether a specified location is within a circle or polygon on a map or whether it lies along a polyline on a map.
@param {kony.map.*} shapeType Contains a Shape Type Constant that defines which kind of shape the location is being tested against.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {String} location Holds a location object which contains lat and lon values.<b>Mandatory</b>
@param {Object} shapeData A key-value pair object that defines the shape using the following keys:
@param {Number} shapeData.radius Radius that is needed to define circle shape. This key is only valid of shapeType is Circle and ignored for other shapes.
@param {Number} shapeData.tolerance [Android]: Specify tolerance in meters when user is interacting with Polyline or Polygon. Not applicable for other shapes.<b>Mandatory</b>
@returns {Boolean}
               * <ul><li>True if the location is within the circle or polygon, or if it lies along the polyline.</li></ul>
@Available Available on Android and iOS.
@access Write
@usage  <pre>var shapeData = {
   locations : [{lat:“17.451759”, lon:“78.380806”},{lat: “17.473305”, lon:”78.425191”}];
   tolerance : 200;
   };
   var location = {lat: “17.427789”, lon:”78.451751”};
   kony.map.containsLocation(kony.map.SHAPE_TYPE_POLYLINE,location, shapeData);     </pre>

