registerForPeekAndPop.!doc:
Registers a widget to enable 3d touch peek and pop gesture.
@param {Function} onPeekCallback - callback, Called when user slightly presses(soft press) the widget. It gets widget, contextInfo as params and shall return preview info table.
@param {Function} onPopCallback - callback, Called when user further presses(hard press) the preview that is displayed for the widget. It gets widget, peekForm as params. This is the place where you need to set content for pop. The form handle returned by this callback is used for pop content. In general, the form that is used for preview has to be used for pop content also. If pop callback is not implement, peek disappears and the app will be taken to its previous state.
 @usage <pre>
   function onPeekCallback(widget, contextInfo) {
     var previewInfoTable = {
       "peekForm": frmSecond,
       "focusRect": [0,0,200,200],
       "contentSize": [320, 480]
     }
     return previewInfoTable;
   }
 </pre>

