clipView.!doc:
     Defines a shape to clip the widget view.
     @property {JSObject}
	 @param {constant} shape  A key-value pair represents a shape of the clipping. You can clip a view as follows: VIEW_CLIP_SHAPE_RECTANGLE: Appears the widget view in rectangular shape. By default, this value is set, VIEW_CLIP_SHAPE_ROUNDED_RECTANGLE: Appears the widget view in rectangular shape with rounded corners, VIEW_CLIP_SHAPE_CIRCLE: Appears the widget view in circular shape.
	 @param {Array.<objects>} bounds A key-value pair represents the bounds of the shape to clip a view. Specify the bounds as an array of integers [left, top, right, bottom].
	 @param {Boolean} boundsInPixel  Defines whether the units of specified bounds should be in pixels or in percentage. The property takes the Boolean value.
	 @param {constant} radius Specifies the radius of the clipping shape. Represents the corner radius of the rounded rectangular shape when clipping shape is VIEW_CLIP_SHAPE_ROUNDED_RECTANGLE or represents the radius of circle when clipping shape is VIEW_CLIP_SHAPE_CIRCLE.
     @Available Android 5.0 and later versions.
     @access Read and Write
	 @usage <pre>
	 //Setting the clipView property<br/>
	 form1.flxCnt1.clipView  = {
		 shape: constants.VIEW_CLIP_SHAPE_CIRCLE,
		 bounds: [5, 5, 5, 5],
		 boundsInPixel: true,
		 radius: 10
        };</pre>

