animate.!doc:
This method applies the animation to the widget immediately, if the widget is part of the currently visible view hierarchy. If widget is not part of the currently visible view hierarchy then this API invocation is ignored. This method is asynchronous and immediately returns and do not wait for the animation to start or complete.
@param {Object} animationObj An object defined using kony.ui.createAnimation() API.<b>Mandatory</b>.
@param {Object} animationConfig An object that contains duration, iterationCount, direction, delay and fillMode.<b>Optional</b>
@param {Number} animationConfig.delay This key defines when the animation will start.
@param {String} animationConfig.direction This key defines whether the animation must play in reverse on some or all cycles.
@param {Number} animationConfig.duration This key defines the time in seconds that an animation takes to complete one cycle.
@param {Number} animationConfig.fillMode This key defines what values are applied to the widget state by the animation outside the time it is executing.
@param {Number} animationConfig.iterationCount This key specifies the number of times an animation cycle is played.
@param {Object} animationCallbacks An object that represents animationStart and animationEnd callbacks.<b>Optional</b>
@param {function} animationCallbacks.animationEnd A JavaScript function that is invoked with the animation ends. For more information, see the Remarks section below.
@param {function} animationCallbacks.animationStart A JavaScript function that is invoked with the animation starts. For more information, see the Remarks section below.
