addCircle.!doc:
This method allows you to add Circle to map widget.
 @param {Object} circleData Specifies the location data for which the circle is drawn on the map
 @param {String} circleData.id  [Mandatory] : Specifies the unique identifier to represent the circle
 @param {JSObject} circleData.centerLocation [Mandatory] : Specifies the center location for circle
 @param {Number} circleData.radius  [Mandatory] : Specifies the radius in meters
 @param {Boolean} circleData.navigateAndZoom  [Optional] : Boolean value to indicate whether the map should be navigated to the circle area and zoom the map to fit the bounds of circle
 @param {Boolean} circleData.showCenterPin  [Optional] : Indicates whether to show pin image for Circle center location
 @param {JSObject} circleData.circleConfig [Optional] : Specifies an object with predefined configuration keys , The following is the list configuration keys:
 @param {String} circleData.circleConfig.lineColor  [All]: Specifies the color of the circle border line in RBGA hex format
 @param {String} circleData.circleConfig.fillColor  [All]: Specifies the color that circle area is filled with in RBGA hex format
 @param {Number} circleData.circleConfig.lineWidth [All]: Specifies the width of the polyline in screen independent pixels
 @param {Array.<numbers>} circleData.circleConfig.lineDashPattern [iOS] : An array of numbers specifying the dash pattern to use for the path
 @param {Number} circleData.zIndex [Optional]: Applicable for Android and iOS platforms.Specifies the stack order of circles added in the Map widget.
 @Available iPhone, android, ipad, andriodtab
@Returns None

addPin.!doc:
 Adds/appends a single pin to map
 @param {Object} pin  An object with possible keys as id, lat, lon, name, desc, etc. <b>Mandatory</b>
 @param {String} pin.id [Mandatory]: Specifies the unique identifier that represents the pin. If a pin already exists with the same identifier, then the id will be replaced by a new id.
 @param {String} pin.lat [Mandatory]: Specifies the latitude of the location.
 @param {String} pin.lon [Mandatory]: Specifies the longitude of the location.
 @param {String} pin.name [Mandatory]: Specifies a short description for the location.
 @param {String} pin.desc [Mandatory]: Specifies a long description for the location.
 @param {String |Image Object} pin.image [Mandatory]: Specifies the map pin image that overrides the defaultPinImage.Refer the Remarks section for more information.
 @param {Boolean} pin.navigateAndZoom [Optional]: Decides whether the navigation to first pin should take place. It is available on Android, Windows, and iOS. The default value of this parameter is true.
 @param {Boolean} pin.showcallout [Optional]: Shows the callout pop-up. The default value is true.
 @param {JSObject} pin.calloutData [Optional]: Specifies the widget data for a given template for a particular location. The value should be a in the form of key-value pairs. The data can have one of the standard keys called template that accepts a reference, to provide location-specific template. This template will override the template provided in the calloutTemplate.
 @param {JSObject} pin.meta [Optional]: Specifies the platform-specific metadata.
 @param {String} pin.meta.color [Optional]: Specifies the color for the pop-up. (Supported on Mobile Web and SPA.)
 @param {String} pin.meta.label [Optional]: Specifies the text for the pop-up. (Supported on Mobile Web and SPA.)
 @param {Number} pin.zIndex [Optional]: Applicable for Android platform only.

 @Available iOS, Android, Windows
 @access Write
 @usage <pre>
var startPt = {
    id : “pin id”,
    lat: "17.4947934",
    lon: "78.3996441",
    name: "KPHB",
    desc: "Kukatpally",
    showCallout : true,
    meta: {
            color: "green",
            label: "A"
    }
};
map.addPin( startPt );</pre>

addPins.!doc:
 Adds/appends multiple pins to map
 @param {Object} pin  An array of pin objects <b>Mandatory</b>
 @param {String} pin.id [Mandatory]: Specifies the unique identifier that represents the pin. If a pin already exists with the same identifier, then the id will be replaced by a new id.
 @param {String} pin.lat [Mandatory]: Specifies the latitude of the location.
 @param {String} pin.lon [Mandatory]: Specifies the longitude of the location.
 @param {String} pin.name [Mandatory]: Specifies a short description for the location.
 @param {String} pin.desc [Mandatory]: Specifies a long description for the location.
 @param {String |Image Object} pin.image [Mandatory]: Specifies the map pin image that overrides the defaultPinImage.Refer the Remarks section for more information.
 @param {Boolean} pin.navigateAndZoom [Optional]: Decides whether the navigation to first pin should take place. It is available on Android, Windows, and iOS. The default value of this parameter is true.
 @param {Boolean} pin.showcallout [Optional]: Shows the callout pop-up. The default value is true.
 @param {JSObject} pin.calloutData [Optional]: Specifies the widget data for a given template for a particular location. The value should be a in the form of key-value pairs. The data can have one of the standard keys called template that accepts a reference, to provide location-specific template. This template will override the template provided in the calloutTemplate.
 @param {JSObject} pin.meta [Optional]: Specifies the platform-specific metadata.
 @param {String} pin.meta.color [Optional]: Specifies the color for the pop-up. (Supported on Mobile Web and SPA.)
 @param {String} pin.meta.label [Optional]: Specifies the text for the pop-up. (Supported on Mobile Web and SPA.)
 @param {Number} pin.zIndex [Optional]: Applicable for Android platform only.

 @Available iOS, Android, Windows
 @access Write
 @usage <pre>
var startPt = {
    id : “pin id”,
    lat: "17.4947934",
    lon: "78.3996441",
    name: "KPHB",
    desc: "Kukatpally",
    showCallout : true,
