};
map.addPins( [startPt] );</pre>

addPolygon.!doc:
This method allows you to add a polygon to the map widget.
@param {Object} polygonData Specifies the location data for which the polygon is drawn on the map
@param {String} polygonData.id  [Mandatory] Specifies the unique identifier to represent the polygon and if a polygon already exists with the same identifier, then it gets replacesd by the new id
@param {Array.<string>} polygonData.locations [Mandatory]  Specifies the list of all the locations as an array
@param {Boolean} polygonData.navigateAndZoom  [Optional]  Boolean value to indicate whether the map should be navigated to the polygon area and zoom the map to fit the bounds of polygon.
@param {JSObject} polygonData.polygonConfig [Optional]  Specifies an object with predefined configuration keys, The following is the list configuration keys
@param {String} polygonData.polygonConfig.lineColor  Specifies the color of the polygon border line in RBGA hex format, Default line color in RGBA is FF0000FF (RED)
@param {String} polygonData.polygonConfig.fillColor Specifies the color that polygon area is filled with in RBGA hex format, The format could be 0xRGBA or RGBA and No fill color is applied by default
@param {Number} polygonData.polygonConfig.lineWidth Specifies the width of the polygon in screen independent pixels, Default line width is 3 dp
@param {Array.<string>} polygonData.polygonConfig.innerPolygons [Android, iOS]: Specifies the list of all the locations as an array to draw inner polygon without fill color
@param {Array.<numbers>} polygonData.polygonConfig.lineDashPattern [iOS] : An array of numbers specifying the dash pattern to use for the path

@Available iPhone, android, ipad, andriodtab
@Returns None

addPolyline.!doc:
This method is used to add a polyline to the map widget with the given location data. You can add multiple polylines to the map widget using this method.
@param {Object} locationData Specifies the location data for which the polyline is drawn on the map. <b>Mandatory</b>
@param {String} locationData.id [Mandatory]:Specifies the unique identifier to represent the polyline. If a polyline already exists with the same identifier, then it gets replacesd by the new id.
@param {String} locationData.startLocation [Optional]:Specifies the location data for the start point of the polyline. The values should be provided as specified in locationData property. The start point of the polyline is represented with a map pin.
@param {String} locationData.endLocation [Optional]:Specifies the location data for the end point of the polyline. The values should be provided as specified in locationData property. The start point of the polyline is represented with a map pin.
@param {Boolean} locationData.navigateAndZoom [Optional]:Boolean value to indicate whether the map should be navigated to the polyline area and zoom the map to fit the bounds of the polyline. If this property is not specified, default value “true” is assumed.
@param {JSObject} locationData.locations  [Optional]:Specifies the list of all the locations as an array including start and end points. Each location object accepts "lat" and "lon" keys and other keys are ignored.
@param {JSObject} locationData.polylineConfig [Optional]:Specifies an object with predefined configuration keys. These configuration keys can hold platform specific keys as well.
@param {String} locationData.polylineConfig.lineColor Specifies the color of the polyline in #RBGA hex format. If the line color property is not specified, by default, Red color is selected. For example, 0xFF0000FF and FF0000FF, both formats are valid for Red color.
@param {Number} locationData.polylineConfig.lineWidth Specifies the width of the polyline in screen independent pixels.
@Available Available on iOS and Android platforms only.
@access Write

